The paper proposes a new architecture for convolutional neural networks (CNNs) that improves their performance on image classification benchmarks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses various design choices for the new architecture, which suggests that it falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the idea of parameter sharing, which is a common technique in deep learning, indicating that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The experiments conducted in the paper involve training and testing CNNs, which could also place it under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with image classification, which is a task related to natural language processing, suggesting that it could also be classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
